    "content": "Come and have a look! First of all, Ctrip wrote that there is a pick-up service, but when I called, no one came to pick me up. Instead, a woman called and told me to walk over for about 3 minutes. Her tone was very impatient! After walking over, I searched for a long time before I found the sign in the first picture, and then there were the corridor and elevator inside. There are big flying cockroaches in the corridor, so be careful! Secondly, the hotel's kettle was rusty, and the hotel's escape window was very small, so you couldn't climb out at all. Only children could climb out. The toilet is very noisy at night, and you can hear the people taking a shower in the next room very clearly. The sound insulation is also very poor at night. Some people are still watching 'Empresses in the Palace' and there are children running around. The sound insulation is very, very, very poor! Moreover, this woman's service attitude was very bad. When she was getting toilet paper, she questioned me, 'Didn't you get it during the day? Why did you use it up so quickly?' Can't you use tissues when you have your period? There was no hand soap or laundry detergent in the room, but there was some at the front desk. I went to get it from the front desk (also the same woman), and she asked me to bring it back to her after use. The service attitude was really bad! It was not until the next day that I saw a male butler. This man was quite polite and spoke more pleasantly! We are all women, why make things so difficult for others? The room is very bad, it's a rental house, not a hotel or a B&B. I really don't recommend booking this one! The lock of the room is not very secure. I suggest you buy something online that can check if there is any surveillance/camera. Avoid lightning!",
