    "business_type": "住宿",
    "content": "Extremely dissatisfied with this stay. 1) The hotel is advertised as being about 250 meters from the pier. I know there are many hotels and guesthouses on Guishan Island, but because an elderly person in our group has mobility issues, we specifically booked one closer to the pier. However, the Zenwood Villa is also located halfway up the mountain! Normally, we have to walk up 5 floors, but this was at least 7-8 floors, and we were carrying several suitcases. We didn't want to come down! The signs were also unclear, making it easy to get lost! At least there should be some indication on the booking page; otherwise, it's like misleading the customer. The front desk even questioned why we hadn't called to confirm. 2) Poor hygiene. A guest's tissues in the bathroom weren't properly cleaned, and there were stains and rat droppings on the walls and corners of the lobby. 3) We booked a three-bedroom villa, but it was actually a four-bedroom villa sold separately. This meant sharing with other guests, which was one thing, but it was baffling that someone else's room key could open my room door in the lobby. Later, we discovered that the Zenwood four-bedroom and three-bedroom villas were in the same villa; they just sold whichever was more popular! 4) The room door was locked after 9:00 PM and there was no room key. I called the front desk and was told that everyone at the hotel had left at 8:00 PM???? Even if guests check in early, there should at least be one person on duty! 5) Regarding security, the master key is somewhere near the villa entrance. Nearby residents could easily find it. Moreover, the villa and the hillside are shared with other hotels and residents, with absolutely no security guards or doormen. Anyone can come and go as they please, yet they dare to leave the room key like that!",
